# lexiprep reverse proxy.
#
# Default site address ":80" serves plain HTTP on the server's IP today — visit
# http://SERVER_IP. No TLS is possible on a bare IP (no hostname to issue a cert for).
#
# When you point a domain here, set SITE_ADDRESS in .env to that hostname, e.g.
#   SITE_ADDRESS=lexiprep.example.com
# and Caddy automatically provisions + renews a Let's Encrypt certificate on :443.
# Also update BETTER_AUTH_URL / WEB_ORIGIN to the https:// domain. Nothing else changes.
{$SITE_ADDRESS::80} {
	encode zstd gzip
	reverse_proxy web:5173
}
